title: Handbook of Eating Disorders
description:
For the second edition of "Handbook of Eating Disorders" (edited by Janet Treasure, Ulrike Schmidt, and Eric van Furth) every chapter was revised and  several new chapters were added to create an up-to-date book on research and clinical experience in this field.
 
In 28 chapters, 52 contributors cover eating disorders from anorexia nervosa and bulimia nervosa to obesity. This book gives a current review (2003) of eating disorders that will be useful for every professional working in this field.
